1.Distinguish between man and whatis command.
ANS:
Man-> displace the manual page off command with full details(syntax, options, description) 
Whatis-> gives the one line description of the command.
Eg:man ls
Eg:ls
Outputslist directory contents

2.use the tee command to save the output of ls -l into a file while also displaying it?
ANS:
In bash ls -l | tee output.txt
->displays the output ls -l on the terminal.
->saves the same output in output.txt.

3. Explain with an example how the tee command can be used in logging.
ANS:
Eg:  in bash
ping -c  4  google.com | tee ping_log.txt
displays the ping result live.
saves a copy in  ping_log.txt for later review.

4.steps to install ubuntu 25.04 LTS on oracle virtual box?
ANS:
1download Ubuntu 25.04 LTS on Oracle VirtualBox.
2open VirtualBox -> click new-> give name example Ubuntu
3choose type = Linux version = Ubuntu 64 bit
4allocate ram example 4GB
5create a virtual disk example 30 GB, VDI format
6—> go to VM settings-> storage-> downloaded ISO file
7start the VM-> open to installer launches.
8select language, keyboard, installation type.
9partition disc automatically or manually.
10complete setup-> restart VM-> Ubuntu 25.04 boots up

5. Kernel panic error during Ubuntu installation( troubleshooting ).
ANS
check ISO integrity: verify download ISI file with checksum.
increse VM resourses: allocate more ram like minimum 2 GB and CPU cores.
Enable virtualization: Ensure VT-x/AMD-V is enabled in BIOS.
change VM settings:
       ~>system ->Enable I/O APIC.
       ~>system->chipset=ICH9.
